summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from Lotta M. Serwe and Phillip L. Serwe, both of Seattle, Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated the 10th day of July, 1908, to All of Lot Four (4) and the following described portions of Lots Five (5), Six (6) and Seven (7), to wit: Commencing at the southeast corner of Lot Seven (7) Thence north along the east line of said Lots Seven (7), Six (6) and Five (5) to the northeast corner of Lot Five (5); thence west along the north line of Lot Five (5) to the northwest corner of said Lot Five (5) thence southeasterly along a straight line across Lots Five (5), Six (6) and Seven (7), to the southeast corner of said Lot Seven (7), the point of beginning, all in Block two (2) of Davis Addition to the City of Seattle.
